	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I was specifically referring to dedicated NES emulators which are in development, not multi-console emulators.  Meaning: "Hi, I'm Jim, I'm 14 years old and I'm making a NES emulator".  "Hi I'm working on my NES emu and I have a thousand questions"...
<br />
<br />There's been tens, if not a hundred, people over the years showing up on this forum talking about how they're doing a NES emulator.  Yet, basically none of them come to fruition.
<br />
<br />My point is more or less to bring to the attention of the masses that no new emulators need to be made -- instead, spend the time/effort to help improve ones already in development or already established.  Or better yet, pick another console altogether; the NES is full.  :)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


